 <img src="http://spacefem.com/uselessquiz/4.gif" border=0>
 </a><br>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=247012> Vani Lala</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unamsundeathmonkey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Namsun DeathMonkey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 842<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/24/02 8:26:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11576.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice on Equipment for 59th Monk</span><hr size=1> You could replace one of your orc fang earrings with a Vah Shir Claw one, they cost somewhere around 3-5k and would be a nice improvement.<br>
<br>
Oiled Greaves run around 15k on Fennin, and are significantly better than black pantherskin.  Or if you're hardcore into HPs, SS or Kael quest pants work well too.<br>
<br>
If your guild is good enough to kill Radir in UP, getting some knotted knuckles would help increase your stats a bit and also boost your dmg output.<br>
<br>
Getting a second chestpiece is also a good idea.  I wear my Icicle Tunic (dropped off Lord Bob) whenever I can do without the regen, because the actual stats on the Fungi really sort of suck.  If your guild can't be persuaded to kill Lord Bob (or those Ice Burrowers in WW for their carapace), a Phase Spider Carapace works pretty well.<br>
<br>
I'm also a 59 monk and our stats pretty close; check out my magelo for some ideas as well. <p><center><IMG SRC=http://namsun.homestead.com/files/eqpics/namsunsig2.jpg><br>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=161080>Celestial Monkey</a> of the 59th Order <br>
Member of <A HREF=http://www.tkagiro.com>T`kagi Ro</A>, Fennin Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujhetlae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jhetlae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/24/02 8:39:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11576.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice on Equipment for 59th Monk</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the input, working on the kael leggings for now(have been for a while) I think i will go for the Black saphire earing, and the bone necklace. I had visions of doing the dragon tooth choker quest, but the bone one is just as easy to get. <br>
<br>
Trying to get a benevo bracer to replace bracer of might.<br>
<br>
As for the shissar headband, not sure if the extra few HP's matter compared to the save magic and the serpent sight on the tranix crown.<br>
<br>
I hate being a blind human =/<br>
<br>
Guild i am in is fairly new, about 20 players 50+<br>
