<br>
Anyway, it's really easy.  Just get the note from Kale, run over to Kael.  There was a guide in the guides section about how to sneak to Wenglawks by yourself, you can use that if you can find it.  If not, just get someone to invis you, run up to Wenglawks, click off invis, turn in the note quickly, and run the hell out (this is what I did <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).<br>
<br>
After that just run back to SS, and turn in the dispelling device you got from Wenglawks to that sentry that he tells you and it'll turn into a giant that you'll need to kill.  I forget the stats exactly, but he'd be super easy if you can get 1 full group with a warrior who has defensive and a cleric.<br>
<br>
Anyhoo, that's how to get a DTC.  Actually though, the clattering bone gives more AC/HP and the DTC gives more resists. <p><center><IMG SRC=http://namsun.homestead.com/files/eqpics/namsunsig2.jpg><br>
