Member of <A HREF=http://www.tkagiro.com>T`kagi Ro</A>, Fennin Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhaganwood.showPublicProfile?language=EN>haganwood</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/25/02 12:39:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11576.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice on Equipment for 59th Monk</span><hr size=1> There are also Bloodclaw Leggings.  10AC, 4INT, 4AGI, 4SvM, 2SvP, and &quot;65HPS&quot;...  Thats the legs I currently wear.  about 30K in Bazaar <p>Rukekak Thunderclaw 51st Iksar Disciple Soulbound On Mith Marr  <br> Haganwood Soulsaver 55th Preserver Soulbound On Mith Marr <br> Kilamana Thunderblade 29th Warrior <br>   Nanelan 29th DE necro </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugaichin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gaichin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/25/02 1:23:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11576.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice on Equipment for 59th Monk</span><hr size=1> IMHO the biggest thing you could do is replace that SoM with a T-staff.  If you have money left over, pick up some lighter shoulders, maybe a wurm-scale coat, replace orc-fang earring, the 2ac 35hp one is nice.  Ditch Djarn's ring for a 6/65 unless you're really close to getting the 'dok or coldain ring.  DT choker, clattering bone, etc. on the neck.  Lookin good otherwise. <p><center>
